## Description
Adds safe area inset padding to fixed elements for iPhone notch/home indicator clearance.

## Problem
- NavBar overlaps iPhone notch in landscape
- Footer covers home indicator on notch devices
- Toasts appear under notch or too close to edges
- Content extends into unsafe areas on edge-to-edge displays

## Solution
- Add `pt-[max(env(safe-area-inset-top),1rem)]` to navbar
- Add `pb-[max(env(safe-area-inset-bottom),1rem)]` to footer
- Add horizontal safe area padding to container
- Add safe area padding to toast notifications
- Use `max()` to ensure minimum 1rem padding even without notch

## Impact
- NavBar stays clear of notch in all orientations
- Footer doesn't cover home indicator
- Toasts appear in safe areas
- Better experience on iPhone 12+ and edge-to-edge Android devices

## Browser Support
- iOS Safari 11.2+ (env variables)
- All modern browsers support env()
- Graceful fallback to 1rem on older browsers

